                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="35959" author="pjones" created="Wed, 2 May 2012 10:16:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the offer. To be honest, actually creating the patches is not the biggest overhead to further extending our support matrix on b1_8. If someone really needs to RHEL6 servers then I would recommend that they use the upcoming 2.1.2. It would be easier for us to accelerate that release than to start extending our support matrix yet further.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="35950" author="simmonsja" created="Wed, 2 May 2012 09:56:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If I did the port would whamcloud be willing to test it and support it? This would be after the 1.8.8 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="35948" author="pjones" created="Wed, 2 May 2012 09:05:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have no plans to add this at the moment - the kernel refresh for b1_8 would be client only.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="35945" author="simmonsja" created="Wed, 2 May 2012 08:12:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will server side support of RHEL6.2 be done for b1_8 &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="35934" author="pjones" created="Tue, 1 May 2012 21:43:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yangsheng&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please take care of this? I would start with b1_8, then b2_1, then master just because of upcoming release schedules.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
